LOIS:  What do you mean

01:24.459 --> 01:27.004
what happens when you die?

01:27.046 --> 01:28.422
You're dead.

01:28.463 --> 01:30.298
That's it.

01:28.463 --> 01:30.298
Oh, now,

01:30.340 --> 01:32.509
honey, that's not quite true.

01:32.551 --> 01:34.053
Actually, son, after death

01:34.093 --> 01:35.136
your body undergoes

01:35.178 --> 01:37.138
a fascinating series of changes.

01:37.180 --> 01:39.182
First, it bloats up

01:37.180 --> 01:39.182
like a balloon.

01:39.224 --> 01:40.809
Then shrivels like a raisin.

01:40.851 --> 01:42.770
Then tiny microbes

01:42.811 --> 01:45.188
you can't even see,

01:42.811 --> 01:45.188
but are on you right now,

01:45.230 --> 01:47.148
start to devour your flesh

01:47.190 --> 01:50.151
and return all the elements

01:47.190 --> 01:50.151
in your body back to the soil.

01:50.193 --> 01:52.153
Now, some people will tell you

01:52.195 --> 01:56.157
that your hair keeps growing,

01:52.195 --> 01:56.157
but that's... that's a myth.

01:56.199 --> 01:58.159
It's actually your head

01:56.199 --> 01:58.159
that shrinks.

01:58.201 --> 02:01.121
Now, go get ready

01:58.201 --> 02:01.121
for Aunt Helen's funeral.

