04:52.584 --> 04:55.336
Nothing? She's dead!

04:52.584 --> 04:55.336
How's Uncle Fred taking it?

04:55.378 --> 04:56.588
Well, I don't think he's thought

04:55.378 --> 04:56.588
too much about it.

04:56.630 --> 04:57.839
He died about two months ago.

04:57.881 --> 04:59.174
What?!

04:57.881 --> 04:59.174
Francis, I'm sorry.

04:59.216 --> 05:01.135
I really have to go. Here.

05:01.176 --> 05:02.803
Talk to your brother.

05:01.176 --> 05:02.803
Mom?

05:02.844 --> 05:04.972
Hello?

05:05.013 --> 05:06.347
All right, let's see it.

05:06.389 --> 05:08.725
I can't breathe.

05:08.767 --> 05:10.227
Fine.

05:10.269 --> 05:11.352
You know the drill.

05:11.394 --> 05:12.437
Upgrade.

05:19.402 --> 05:21.280
See?

05:21.321 --> 05:23.240
Problem solved.

05:23.282 --> 05:25.033
Hello?

05:25.075 --> 05:26.034
Oh.

05:26.076 --> 05:27.786
Okay, well, you can wear

05:27.828 --> 05:30.289
one of the suits that

05:27.828 --> 05:30.289
Uncle Fred left you.

05:30.330 --> 05:32.207
Aw, Mom, a dead suit?

05:32.249 --> 05:35.460
Cool. A dead suit.

05:37.838 --> 05:40.757
Dewey, why don't you help

05:37.838 --> 05:40.757
your little friend

05:40.799 --> 05:42.383
find his way out?

05:40.799 --> 05:42.383
I did.

05:42.425 --> 05:44.385
He keeps coming back.

05:48.431 --> 05:50.475
This thing's

05:48.431 --> 05:50.475
