07:18.563 --> 07:21.316
Mom, I hate wearing

07:18.563 --> 07:21.316
Reese's hand-me-downs.

07:21.358 --> 07:22.943
Look at this.

07:22.984 --> 07:25.904
Jelly in the pockets,

07:22.984 --> 07:25.904
the fly's broken,

07:25.946 --> 07:28.365
and it smells like wet dog.

07:28.407 --> 07:31.076
Well, you should be glad

07:28.407 --> 07:31.076
he only wore it once.

07:31.118 --> 07:33.328
You know, I'm trying

07:31.118 --> 07:33.328
to be there for Mom.

07:33.370 --> 07:36.331
But the annoyances are starting

07:33.370 --> 07:36.331
to outweigh the guilt.

07:36.373 --> 07:38.499
I'm this close to sneaking

07:36.373 --> 07:38.499
out of the whole thing.

07:38.541 --> 07:41.502
Well, I suppose you're

07:38.541 --> 07:41.502
entitled to complain.

07:41.544 --> 07:44.798
After all, it's

07:41.544 --> 07:44.798
only my Aunt Helen.

07:44.839 --> 07:47.384
What is she-- a mind reader?

07:47.426 --> 07:49.510
And then there were

07:47.426 --> 07:49.510
ants on her bones.

07:49.552 --> 07:51.763
And the police came.

07:49.552 --> 07:51.763
Dad, listen...

07:51.805 --> 07:54.515
Hey, can you think of anything

07:51.805 --> 07:54.515
that rhymes with cadaver?

07:51.805 --> 07:54.515
Dad?

07:54.557 --> 07:56.184
How long is this

07:54.557 --> 07:56.184
funeral gonna take?

07:56.226 --> 07:57.602
Including traveling time?

07:56.226 --> 07:57.602
All day.

07:57.644 --> 07:58.937
(groans)

07:58.979 --> 08:00.105
I know, I know.

07:58.979 --> 08:00.105
But remember,

08:00.147 --> 08:01.522
it'll make your mom happy.

08:01.564 --> 08:03.733
Mom really loved

08:01.564 --> 08:03.733
Aunt Helen, huh?

08:03.775 --> 08:05.526
Oh, God, no.

08:05.568 --> 08:06.820
Your mom hated her.

08:06.861 --> 08:09.448
What? She "hated her"?

08:06.861 --> 08:09.448
Mm-hmm.

08:09.489 --> 08:11.532
Everyone did.

08:09.489 --> 08:11.532
Horrible woman.

08:11.574 --> 08:13.034
I used to have to forbid her

08:11.574 --> 08:13.034
from calling here

08:13.076 --> 08:15.329
'cause she always

08:13.076 --> 08:15.329
made your mom cry.

08:15.370 --> 08:17.414
I can't believe Mom

08:15.370 --> 08:17.414
tricked me like that.

08:17.456 --> 08:19.040
I'll tell you one thing--

08:19.082 --> 08:20.541
I now consider myself

08:19.082 --> 08:20.541
totally free

08:20.583 --> 08:22.543
to ditch this funeral.

08:22.585 --> 08:24.587
I got to call Julie.

08:25.630 --> 08:27.257
Hello?

08:25.630 --> 08:27.257
Malcolm!

08:27.299 --> 08:29.550
Oh, thank God!

08:27.299 --> 08:29.550
Somebody I can talk to.

08:29.592 --> 08:30.635
Sorry, I have to make a call.

08:30.677 --> 08:32.095
No...

08:30.677 --> 08:32.095
(dial tone drones)

08:36.599 --> 08:38.977
So, your aunt's... not dead?

08:39.019 --> 08:40.561
No. It turned out to be

08:39.019 --> 08:40.561
one of those comas

08:40.603 --> 08:42.356
where they think you're dead

08:42.397 --> 08:44.024
and they put you

08:42.397 --> 08:44.024
on the embalmer's table

08:44.065 --> 08:45.566
and you wake up

08:44.065 --> 08:45.566
at the last second.

08:45.608 --> 08:47.568
It was a close call.

08:47.610 --> 08:48.820
Uh, okay.

08:48.862 --> 08:50.571
I guess we'll pick you up

08:48.862 --> 08:50.571
at 2:00.

08:50.613 --> 08:52.573
Great.

08:52.615 --> 08:55.035
I figure I'll commit to it first

08:52.615 --> 08:55.035
and come up with a plan later.

08:55.076 --> 08:57.578
I always think better

08:55.076 --> 08:57.578
under pressure...

08:57.620 --> 09:00.790
or is it when

08:57.620 --> 09:00.790
I'm not under pressure?

09:00.832 --> 09:03.584
Oh, well. Too late now.

09:03.626 --> 09:05.795
I'm ready to go.

09:03.626 --> 09:05.795
Yeah. Hey!

09:05.837 --> 09:07.588
You're taking a backpack

09:05.837 --> 09:07.588
to the funeral?

09:07.630 --> 09:09.590
My back gets cold.

09:09.632 --> 09:11.009
Fair enough.

09:11.051 --> 09:12.802
LOIS:

09:11.051 --> 09:12.802
Look, Francis,

09:12.844 --> 09:15.305
I guess I get scattered.

09:12.844 --> 09:15.305
You know, sometimes I forget

09:15.347 --> 09:17.307
what I told you, and you're

09:15.347 --> 09:17.307
not here, so I don't...

09:17.349 --> 09:19.600
I'm not there

09:17.349 --> 09:19.600
because you sent me away.

09:19.642 --> 09:22.479
I swear, I'm not even

09:19.642 --> 09:22.479
a part of this family anymore.

09:22.521 --> 09:24.647
Francis, it's very important

09:22.521 --> 09:24.647
that you understand

09:24.689 --> 09:26.233
that is  not  true.

09:26.274 --> 09:28.609
But I don't have time right now.

09:26.274 --> 09:28.609
I understand.

09:28.651 --> 09:30.695
It's not like it's a matter

09:28.651 --> 09:30.695
of life and death.

09:30.737 --> 09:32.613
Oh, wait, it is!

09:32.655 --> 09:33.907
Anyone else die in the last

09:32.655 --> 09:33.907
five minutes

09:33.948 --> 09:35.283
I should know about?

09:35.325 --> 09:36.617
Francis, you want

09:35.325 --> 09:36.617
to know everything

09:36.659 --> 09:37.785
that's been happening?

09:37.827 --> 09:39.246
Your father mowed the lawn,

09:39.287 --> 09:40.621
Reese polished off

09:39.287 --> 09:40.621
all the cereal,

09:40.663 --> 09:41.706
and I dropped a frying pan

09:40.663 --> 09:41.706
on my foot

09:41.748 --> 09:43.124
and I got a big black toe.

09:43.166 --> 09:44.625
You want me to send a picture?

09:47.295 --> 09:49.214
Egg! Cut it out!

09:49.256 --> 09:50.631
Who is Egg?

09:50.673 --> 09:52.633
Oh, he's a new boy in the house.

09:52.675 --> 09:53.634
What?!

09:53.676 --> 09:55.011
Okay.

09:55.053 --> 09:56.471
It'll only hurt for a second

09:56.513 --> 09:59.099
and I'll get out of the funeral.

09:59.140 --> 10:01.642
I can tell Julie

09:59.140 --> 10:01.642
a really cool story

10:01.684 --> 10:04.187
about how I got my black eye.

10:06.898 --> 10:09.650
Aw, I'm so gutless!

10:09.692 --> 10:11.486
Why are you taking so long?

10:11.528 --> 10:12.487
Let's go.

10:12.529 --> 10:13.654
Reese, listen.

10:13.696 --> 10:14.822
I know it sounds crazy,

10:14.864 --> 10:16.657
but I need you to hit me.

10:16.699 --> 10:17.658
(groans)

10:17.700 --> 10:19.286
You idiot!

10:19.327 --> 10:20.661
In the eye!

10:20.703 --> 10:22.080
And leave a mark

10:20.703 --> 10:22.080
for Mom to see?

10:22.122 --> 10:23.664
Forget it.

10:23.706 --> 10:25.666
No bruises, no evidence...

10:25.708 --> 10:27.294
no crime.

10:27.335 --> 10:29.670
(sighs)

10:29.712 --> 10:33.467
I guess we move on

10:29.712 --> 10:33.467
to plan B-- lying.

10:33.508 --> 10:34.468
What book report?

10:34.509 --> 10:35.676
I just remembered.

10:35.718 --> 10:37.137
I have a big book report

10:35.718 --> 10:37.137
due tomorrow.

10:37.178 --> 10:39.473
And I haven't even

10:37.178 --> 10:39.473
started reading it.

10:39.514 --> 10:40.890
Standard technique--

10:40.932 --> 10:42.517
you volunteer a small crime

10:42.559 --> 10:45.270
to distract them

10:42.559 --> 10:45.270
from looking for the big one.

10:45.312 --> 10:46.687
So, what's the report on?

10:46.729 --> 10:47.730
A Tale of Two Cities.

10:47.772 --> 10:50.191
Oh, how many words?

10:47.772 --> 10:50.191
750.

10:50.233 --> 10:52.360
Was that on your

10:50.233 --> 10:52.360
assignment sheet?

10:50.233 --> 10:52.360
No, it's an addendum.

10:52.402 --> 10:54.362
When did you get that?

10:52.402 --> 10:54.362
Thursday.

10:52.402 --> 10:54.362
I didn't bring it home.

10:54.404 --> 10:56.323
That's why I forgot

10:54.404 --> 10:56.323
to do the assignment.

10:56.364 --> 10:57.740
Ooh, nice one.

10:57.782 --> 11:00.701
Well, I suppose

10:57.782 --> 11:00.701
if it's schoolwork.

11:00.743 --> 11:01.953
That's the mislead.

11:01.995 --> 11:03.580
Wait for the reverse.

11:03.622 --> 11:05.706
A Tale of Two Cities.

11:05.748 --> 11:07.708
Who's that by?

11:05.748 --> 11:07.708
Charles Dickens.

11:07.750 --> 11:10.629
Oh, I thought it was

11:07.750 --> 11:10.629
Victor Hugo.

11:07.750 --> 11:10.629
No, it's Dickens.

11:10.670 --> 11:12.005
Is that the one

11:10.670 --> 11:12.005
with Jean Valjean?

11:12.046 --> 11:14.715
That's  Les Miserables.

11:12.046 --> 11:14.715
No, no.

11:14.757 --> 11:16.717
Uh, isn't  A Tale of Two Cities

11:14.757 --> 11:16.717
the one with Jean Valjean,

11:16.759 --> 11:19.095
where he's says, "It's a far,

11:16.759 --> 11:19.095
far better thing I do..."

11:19.137 --> 11:21.014
right before he steals

11:19.137 --> 11:21.014
a loaf of bread?

11:21.055 --> 11:23.724
No. Sidney Carton says that

11:21.055 --> 11:23.724
right before they behead him.

11:23.766 --> 11:25.726
I thought you hadn't read it.

11:25.768 --> 11:28.729
What? No. I said

11:25.768 --> 11:28.729
I hadn't  written  it.

11:28.771 --> 11:29.772
And when is it due?

11:29.814 --> 11:31.024
Tomorrow, I told you.

11:31.065 --> 11:32.942
On  Les Miserables?

11:31.065 --> 11:32.942
Yes. No!

11:32.984 --> 11:34.735
It's on  Tale of Two Cities.

11:34.777 --> 11:36.237
Which you haven't read yet.

11:34.777 --> 11:36.237
Right.

11:36.279 --> 11:37.905
But you just said you did.

11:37.947 --> 11:41.242
No, I-I said I didn't,

11:37.947 --> 11:41.242
and then you said...

11:41.284 --> 11:43.744
It was Thursday, and...

11:43.786 --> 11:46.747
Look, I just don't want to go

11:43.786 --> 11:46.747
to this stupid funeral!

11:46.789 --> 11:48.749
There's no reason for me

11:46.789 --> 11:48.749
to go, and I want to go

11:48.791 --> 11:50.835
to the concert with Julie!

11:48.791 --> 11:50.835
REESE:

11:48.791 --> 11:50.835
Let's go, let's go.

11:50.877 --> 11:52.587
I'll be waiting in the car.

11:52.629 --> 11:53.796
LOIS:

11:52.629 --> 11:53.796
Malcolm?

11:53.838 --> 11:55.756
I am ashamed of you.

11:55.798 --> 11:58.426
Wanting to deny your

11:55.798 --> 11:58.426
poor Aunt Helen her due.

11:58.468 --> 12:00.428
No, that won't work on me,

11:58.468 --> 12:00.428
because I know

12:00.470 --> 12:02.556
you didn't love Aunt Helen.

12:00.470 --> 12:02.556
You hated her!

12:02.597 --> 12:04.765
Of course I hated her. What does

12:02.597 --> 12:04.765
that have to do with anything?

12:04.807 --> 12:06.767
What?

12:04.807 --> 12:06.767
Malcolm, this isn't about love.

12:06.809 --> 12:08.478
It's about family.

12:08.520 --> 12:09.770
We have a duty to this family.

12:09.812 --> 12:11.565
And we are darn well

12:09.812 --> 12:11.565
gonna do it!

12:11.606 --> 12:13.567
(car horn honking)

12:11.606 --> 12:13.567
But why? It's not fair!

12:13.608 --> 12:15.776
You can't just stick the word

12:13.608 --> 12:15.776
"family" in front of something

12:15.818 --> 12:17.571
and turn everyone

12:15.818 --> 12:17.571
else into slaves.

12:17.612 --> 12:19.155
It makes no sense.

12:19.197 --> 12:20.781
No one liked this woman.

12:20.823 --> 12:22.783
So why do we have to

12:20.823 --> 12:22.783
pretend like we did now?

12:22.825 --> 12:25.078
What good will it do anybody?

12:25.119 --> 12:27.622
Hal?

12:27.664 --> 12:29.832
I got nothing.

12:29.874 --> 12:31.792
I could really use

12:29.874 --> 12:31.792
some support here.

12:31.834 --> 12:32.835
Excuse me?

12:32.877 --> 12:34.795
I am being

12:32.877 --> 12:34.795
incredibly supportive.

12:34.837 --> 12:37.424
I'm giving up my entire day

12:34.837 --> 12:37.424
for this-this thing.

12:37.465 --> 12:39.384
And you don't hear me

12:37.465 --> 12:39.384
complaining.

12:39.426 --> 12:40.885
Hal, it was a bunch

12:39.426 --> 12:40.885
of old record albums.

12:40.927 --> 12:42.887
It's not like you're not giving

12:40.927 --> 12:42.887
up something important.

12:42.929 --> 12:44.805
Well, they're important to me.

12:44.847 --> 12:46.224
LOIS (sighs):

12:44.847 --> 12:46.224
You-you people!

12:46.266 --> 12:47.684
I can't believe you.

12:47.726 --> 12:49.185
I asked you to do

12:47.726 --> 12:49.185
one thing that...

12:49.227 --> 12:51.062
FRANCIS: You're not asking;

12:49.227 --> 12:51.062
you're ordering.

12:52.897 --> 12:54.815
LOIS:

12:52.897 --> 12:54.815
After all I do for this family.

12:54.857 --> 12:57.818
I cook, I clean,

12:54.857 --> 12:57.818
I spackle, I plunge.

12:57.860 --> 13:00.113
And none of it means anything

12:57.860 --> 13:00.113
to any of you people!

13:00.154 --> 13:02.823
And the one time

13:00.154 --> 13:02.823
I ask you for something--

13:02.865 --> 13:04.825
something that I shouldn't even

13:02.865 --> 13:04.825
have to ask you for--

13:04.867 --> 13:06.286
and all I get are complaints!

13:06.327 --> 13:09.122
(horn honking louder)

13:09.163 --> 13:11.874
Well, what about me, hmm?

13:11.916 --> 13:14.085
You think I want to be

13:11.916 --> 13:14.085
cleaning out the gutters

13:14.127 --> 13:16.129
when I could be

13:14.127 --> 13:16.129
surfing the beaches of Europe

13:16.170 --> 13:19.215
or-or cruising around on my hog?

13:19.257 --> 13:20.841
What hog?!

13:19.257 --> 13:20.841
Aha!

13:20.883 --> 13:22.885
Exactly! Where's my hog?!

13:22.927 --> 13:25.430
(sighs)

13:22.927 --> 13:25.430
Where do you think you're going?

13:25.472 --> 13:26.723
I have had it!

13:26.765 --> 13:28.849
From now on,

13:26.765 --> 13:28.849
no one has to do anything.

13:28.891 --> 13:30.143
We can all just do

13:28.891 --> 13:30.143
whatever we want!

13:30.184 --> 13:31.852
And I want to take

13:31.894 --> 13:33.854
a bubble bath!

13:33.896 --> 13:35.814
Fine!

13:37.900 --> 13:41.362
So, that's a "yes"

13:37.900 --> 13:41.362
on the concert?

13:47.910 --> 13:50.413
Come on, come on.

13:53.291 --> 13:54.875
(sighs)

13:54.917 --> 13:56.795
Are you gonna be

13:54.917 --> 13:56.795
in there all day?

13:56.835 --> 13:58.672
If I feel like it.

13:58.713 --> 14:00.881
Fine. Just so you know,

13:58.713 --> 14:00.881
when I'm done in the garage,

14:00.923 --> 14:03.884
I'm using the bathroom

14:00.923 --> 14:03.884
whether you're in here or not.

14:05.804 --> 14:07.681
Mom?

14:07.722 --> 14:09.599
I think we should go

14:07.722 --> 14:09.599
to Aunt Helen's funeral.

14:09.641 --> 14:11.309
I mean,

14:09.641 --> 14:11.309
she was a good woman.

14:11.351 --> 14:12.893
It's the least we can do.

14:12.935 --> 14:14.145
I don't know

14:12.935 --> 14:14.145
what you're trying to pull,

14:14.187 --> 14:15.480
Reese, but I don't like it.

14:15.522 --> 14:17.482
Am I the only one

14:15.522 --> 14:17.482
that cared about her?

14:17.524 --> 14:18.566
Yes, you're the good one.

14:18.608 --> 14:19.609
Enjoy your moment in the sun.

14:19.651 --> 14:20.901
Now, get out of here.

14:20.943 --> 14:23.112
This is me time.

14:23.154 --> 14:24.614
(sniffing)

14:24.656 --> 14:28.326
Hey, Reese,

14:24.656 --> 14:28.326
which one stinks more?

14:28.368 --> 14:30.495
What's your problem?!

14:30.537 --> 14:33.498
You couldn't keep your big mouth

14:30.537 --> 14:33.498
shut until after the funeral.

14:33.540 --> 14:34.957
Now I'll have to wait

14:33.540 --> 14:34.957
for another relative

14:34.999 --> 14:36.209
to die to bury this thing.

14:36.250 --> 14:37.627
It could be weeks!

14:37.669 --> 14:38.919
You'll think of something.

14:38.961 --> 14:40.129
No, I won't.

14:40.171 --> 14:42.173
You have good ideas

14:40.171 --> 14:42.173
all the time.

14:42.215 --> 14:44.509
But for me, this was special.

14:44.551 --> 14:46.969
Hey! You can't leave

14:44.551 --> 14:46.969
this mess here.

14:47.011 --> 14:48.429
I've got a guest coming over.

14:48.471 --> 14:50.181
Too bad.

14:48.471 --> 14:50.181
Thanks to you,

14:50.223 --> 14:52.016
no one has to do

14:50.223 --> 14:52.016
anything anymore.

14:52.058 --> 14:53.934
It's anarchy, baby.

14:53.976 --> 14:55.812
That's the word, right?

14:55.854 --> 14:57.938
(sighs)

15:00.692 --> 15:03.236
Um... Mom?

15:03.277 --> 15:04.987
I was just wondering

15:05.029 --> 15:06.947
if you could wash

15:05.029 --> 15:06.947
this shirt for me?

15:06.989 --> 15:08.949
(laughing)

15:08.991 --> 15:10.660
You must be joking.

15:10.702 --> 15:11.952
But you're the only one

15:10.702 --> 15:11.952
that knows how to use

15:11.994 --> 15:13.954
the washer and dryer

15:11.994 --> 15:13.954
without getting shocked.

15:13.996 --> 15:15.373
Please?

15:15.415 --> 15:18.918
Well... since you said please.

15:23.005 --> 15:24.965
Here you go.

15:25.007 --> 15:26.926
All washed.

15:29.220 --> 15:32.014
I think you've been

15:29.220 --> 15:32.014
in the garage long enough.

15:32.056 --> 15:34.975
(chuckling)

15:35.017 --> 15:36.477
Okay.

15:37.854 --> 15:40.022
Gosh!

15:40.064 --> 15:42.149
Well, no, no, no.

15:42.191 --> 15:44.485
You are gonna get

15:42.191 --> 15:44.485
your own outlet.

15:44.527 --> 15:47.988
Uh... okay, here we go.

15:48.030 --> 15:51.992
Okay... okay, here we are.

15:52.034 --> 15:54.287
(laughing)

15:59.041 --> 16:00.376
(grunting)

16:00.418 --> 16:02.921
Come on.

16:02.962 --> 16:04.714
Come on. God.

16:04.756 --> 16:06.340
Gotcha!

16:07.884 --> 16:08.968
Oh.

16:10.219 --> 16:14.014
No, not my problem today.

16:14.056 --> 16:16.309
(chuckling)

16:19.145 --> 16:21.230
(music playing loudly)

16:27.069 --> 16:31.240
♪ Well, I don't know

16:27.069 --> 16:31.240
why I came here tonight ♪

16:31.282 --> 16:34.869
♪ I got a feeling

16:31.282 --> 16:34.869
that something ain't right... ♪

16:34.911 --> 16:36.078
Hand me that loofah.

16:36.120 --> 16:39.081
He wants juice.

16:39.123 --> 16:40.750
Go get your own juice.

16:40.792 --> 16:42.460
You said I'm not supposed to.

16:42.502 --> 16:44.420
(sighing):

16:42.502 --> 16:44.420
You're right.

16:44.462 --> 16:46.088
Okay, from now on,

16:46.130 --> 16:48.633
you are officially old enough

16:46.130 --> 16:48.633
to get your own juice.

16:48.675 --> 16:52.052
Poof.

16:52.094 --> 16:54.054
♪ Yes, I'm stuck

16:52.094 --> 16:54.054
in the middle with you ♪

16:54.096 --> 16:56.766
♪ And I'm wondering

16:54.096 --> 16:56.766
what it is I should do... ♪

16:56.808 --> 16:58.893
Darn it.

16:59.811 --> 17:01.896
Darn it.

17:03.147 --> 17:04.231
Darn it.

17:04.273 --> 17:05.650
Mom!

17:05.692 --> 17:06.776
I spilled!

17:06.818 --> 17:09.069
So? Clean it up!

17:09.111 --> 17:11.364
♪ Jokers to the right,

17:09.111 --> 17:11.364
here I am ♪

17:11.405 --> 17:13.741
♪ Stuck in the middle with you ♪

17:13.783 --> 17:16.744
♪ Well, you started off

17:13.783 --> 17:16.744
with nothing... ♪

17:16.786 --> 17:18.705
(sniffs)

17:18.746 --> 17:20.540
Green apple soap.

17:20.581 --> 17:24.168
Girls like green apples, right?

17:24.210 --> 17:28.923
Oh, man,

17:24.210 --> 17:28.923
she got my pants wet, too!

17:28.965 --> 17:30.257
♪ Here I am, stuck

17:28.965 --> 17:30.257
in the middle with you... ♪

17:30.299 --> 17:32.844
Hello?

17:34.929 --> 17:37.181
Is Malcolm here?

17:37.223 --> 17:38.265
(gasps)

17:38.307 --> 17:39.559
Is Malcolm here?!

17:39.600 --> 17:40.601
Huh?

17:40.643 --> 17:42.729
Malcolm!

17:59.078 --> 18:00.079
JULIE:

17:59.078 --> 18:00.079
Malcolm?

18:05.960 --> 18:08.128
Julie!

18:05.960 --> 18:08.128
Nothing.

18:08.170 --> 18:11.799
♪ On the back and say please ♪

18:11.841 --> 18:14.427
♪ Please... ♪

18:14.468 --> 18:15.970
(screaming)

18:16.012 --> 18:17.179
(grunts)

18:17.221 --> 18:19.640
Oh, my God!

18:19.682 --> 18:20.850
Are you okay?

18:20.892 --> 18:22.142
I just wanted to be nice!

18:22.184 --> 18:24.144
People told me not

18:22.184 --> 18:24.144
to come to your house!

18:24.186 --> 18:26.355
But I thought they

18:24.186 --> 18:26.355
were just being silly!

18:26.397 --> 18:27.815
Julie, I'm sorry!

18:27.857 --> 18:29.358
Things aren't

18:27.857 --> 18:29.358
usually like this.

18:29.400 --> 18:32.152
Just give me a minute

18:29.400 --> 18:32.152
and I'll be ready to go.

18:32.194 --> 18:33.237
I don't want to go anymore!

18:33.279 --> 18:34.614
Just leave me alone!

18:34.655 --> 18:37.075
♪ Out of my chair ♪

18:37.116 --> 18:38.659
♪ And I'm wondering

18:37.116 --> 18:38.659
how I'll get down the stairs ♪

18:38.701 --> 18:40.661
(record scratches)

18:40.703 --> 18:42.872
How could you let her see me

18:40.703 --> 18:42.872
in my underwear?!

18:46.125 --> 18:48.086
Mom, this has gone too far!

18:48.127 --> 18:49.378
You have to do something!

18:49.420 --> 18:51.464
It's not supposed

18:49.420 --> 18:51.464
to be like this.

18:51.505 --> 18:53.549
We're not supposed

18:51.505 --> 18:53.549
to injure my friends.

18:53.591 --> 18:56.218
We're not supposed to let people

18:53.591 --> 18:56.218
see me in my underpants!

18:56.260 --> 18:58.805
We're supposed to be there

18:56.260 --> 18:58.805
for each other.

18:58.846 --> 19:00.180
Like when a family member dies,

19:00.222 --> 19:01.474
and we're supposed to go

19:00.222 --> 19:01.474
to their funeral?

19:01.515 --> 19:04.477
(sighs)

19:01.515 --> 19:04.477
I'll be in my room.

19:16.114 --> 19:18.240
Then she slid into the trash

19:16.114 --> 19:18.240
and ran off.

19:18.282 --> 19:21.661
I swear, this whole family

19:18.282 --> 19:21.661
is falling apart.

19:21.702 --> 19:24.122
Oh, yes! I knew

19:21.702 --> 19:24.122
this moment would come.

19:24.163 --> 19:25.873
They don't have

19:24.163 --> 19:25.873
their scapegoat around,

19:25.915 --> 19:27.708
so everything goes to hell.

19:27.750 --> 19:30.210
No one realized that I'm the one

19:27.750 --> 19:30.210
who held this family together.

19:30.252 --> 19:32.296
Without me

19:30.252 --> 19:32.296
to blame everything on,

19:32.338 --> 19:34.214
they don't know what to do

19:32.338 --> 19:34.214
with themselves.

19:34.256 --> 19:35.633
A scapegoat... thanks.

19:35.675 --> 19:37.217
Mom thinks...

19:37.259 --> 19:38.218
He's right.

19:38.260 --> 19:40.429
This family needs a scapegoat.

19:40.471 --> 19:44.224
I started this, so I should be

19:40.471 --> 19:44.224
the one to end it.

19:52.191 --> 19:55.069
I did a terrible thing today.

19:55.111 --> 19:56.946
I tore this family apart.

19:56.988 --> 19:58.739
And I'm really sorry for that.

19:58.781 --> 20:00.908
But...

20:00.950 --> 20:03.577
it's not half as bad...

20:00.950 --> 20:03.577
as what Reese did!

20:07.581 --> 20:10.668
Oh, my God!

20:10.710 --> 20:12.712
(distorted): I'm Mighty Man.

20:10.710 --> 20:12.712
Was this Dewey's present?

20:12.753 --> 20:14.254
DEWEY:

20:12.753 --> 20:14.254
Present?

20:14.296 --> 20:15.255
LOIS:

20:14.296 --> 20:15.255
Reese, how could you?

20:15.297 --> 20:17.299
Do you know how

20:15.297 --> 20:17.299
expensive this was?

20:17.341 --> 20:18.968
Hal?

20:17.341 --> 20:18.968
I'm on it.

20:19.010 --> 20:20.553
That was a terrible thing to do

20:20.594 --> 20:22.262
to your little brother.

20:20.594 --> 20:22.262
There's more!

20:22.304 --> 20:24.140
He was gonna bury it

20:22.304 --> 20:24.140
with Aunt Helen!

20:24.182 --> 20:27.143
You were going to make

20:24.182 --> 20:27.143
Aunt Helen spend eternity

20:27.185 --> 20:28.310
with a crushed Mighty Man?

